<h1>Problem 663 - 2010 IMO, P6 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(a_1, a_2, a_3, \ldots\) be a sequence of positive real numbers, and \(s\) be a positive integer, such that
\[a_n = \max \{ a_k + a_{n-k} \mid 1 \leq k \leq n-1 \} \ \textrm{ for all } \ n > s.\]
Prove there exist positive integers \(\ell \leq s\) and \(N\), such that
\[a_n = a_{\ell} + a_{n - \ell} \ \textrm{ for all } \ n \geq N.\]</p>
